ax^2+bx+c = 0\space
px^2+qx+r = 0\space
\alpha, \beta
\gamma,\delta
\frac{\alpha}{\beta} = \frac{\gamma}{\delta}=k
k \in \mathbb{Q}
(|b|-\sqrt{b^2-4ac})/(|b|+\sqrt{b^2-4ac})
ac/b^2
ac\cdot q^2=pr\cdot b^2
(*)
D=b^2-4ac
\Delta=q^2-4pr
(*)
b^2\cdot\Delta=q^2\cdot D
x_1+x_2=\frac{-b}{a}
x_1x_2=\frac{c}{a}
x_1^2+2x_1x_2+x_2^2=\frac{b^2}{a^2}
x_1x_2
\frac{x_1}{x_2}+\frac{x_2}{x_1}+2=\frac{b^2}{ac} \Rightarrow\frac{x_1}{x_2}+\frac{x_2}{x_1}-2=\frac{\Delta_1}{ac} \Rightarrow k+\frac{1}{k}-2=\frac{\Delta_1}{ac}
k+\frac{1}{k}-2=\frac{\Delta_2}{pr}
\frac{\Delta_1}{\Delta_2}=\frac{ac}{pr}
